{% set demoTitle %}How to center a div with flexbox{% endset %}
{% set description %}
There are different ways of centering a div with css.
One of the easiest ways is to make the parent container a flex container.
Then use the properties <mark class="highlight">justify-content</mark> and <mark class="highlight">align-items</mark> to center the children within this container.
{% endset %}

{% set open = true %}

{% set html %}
<div class="flex-container">
  <div>some content</div>
</div>
{% endset %}

{% set css %}
.flex-container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  min-height: 30vh;
}
{% endset %}

