{% set demoTitle %}How to center a div with css-grid{% endset %}

{% set description %}
Another way of centering a div is by using css-grid.
Now you have to give the parent container a display of grid.
Then use the property <mark class="highlight">place-content</mark> to center the children of this container.
{% endset %}

{% set open = true %}

{% set html %}
<div class="grid-container">
  <div>some content</div>
</div>
{% endset %}

{% set css %}
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  place-content: center;
  min-height: 30vh;
}
{% endset %}

